Description: Be build B2B content engines that drive revenue by helping businesses resonate with their ideal customers.
Headquarters Regions: Western US
Full Description: We help B2B organizations build content engines that drive revenue.  What’s a content engine? It’s a system for transforming customer insights and business expertise into powerful content that resonates with your audience until they buy. Most marketing efforts feel like arts and crafts. We fix that.  Our sprints establish marketing as a core business function that fuels qualified sales opportunities. Here’s how: 1. Customer Research: We research your business, current customers, competitors, and market to identify your best customers (ICP). And how to best reach them. 2. Sales + Marketing Alignment: We help your business set up systems and processes that collect critical customer data without bogging down your sales team. 3. Optimize the Buyer’s Journey: We evaluate all the touch points in your buyer’s journey. And we help you optimize for a frictionless, human experience that increases sales opportunities. 4. Capture Existing Demand: We figure out what’s working and what’s not on your website. Then we build an actionable SEO Roadmap to help you rank for keywords that drive sales and business growth. 5. Generate New Demand: We work with your team to create assets, share thought leadership, and lead events that WOW your customers.
Industry Groups: Advertising, Internet Services, Sales and Marketing

Description: Brown Eyed Baker it’s perfectly acceptable to eat dessert first!.
Headquarters Regions: Great Lakes, Northeastern US
Full Description: Back in February of 2007, I was living a couple of hours away from friends and family, and winter claustrophobia had begun to set in when I stumbled across a food blog online. I had always loved to bake (a gene my mom claims skipped a generation and went straight from my grandma to me) and enjoyed writing, so this seemed like a perfect way to escape the grey winter days. I figured it would be a creative outlet, perhaps nudge me to try some new, more challenging recipes, and my mom and sister could check out what I was making. That was nearly seven years ago and the rest, as they say, is history. What an amazing journey this has been! What you’ll find here are some of my favorite food groups: desserts, appetizers and loads of comfort food, all made primarily from scratch. My hope is that you leave the site with the insatiable urge to run into your kitchen and whip up what you’ve seen here, and the confidence to know that you can do it. Growing up in an Italian family, the kitchen was always the hub of activity – it’s where everyone gathered to talk, eat and share life while amazing food was being created. I am so happy to have you here in my virtual kitchen and hope you’ll return again and again

VINTU’s mission: profitable growth by providing products and services that are eco-friendly and offer superior value to the consumer, through a dedication to superior customer service, innovation, quality and commitment.     Company Goals and Objectives:    The goals of VINTU are to: 1) improve the quality of life for all consumers, 2) be the market leader in category, 3)design and create products that have the reputation as being of high quality and thus develop a loyal customer following, 4) maintain solid sales growth and profitability via innovation and superior marketing methods.    I am seeking investor funding to help launch a new product in the U.S./North America. The product is called "Inchworm Slider", a unique fitness product recently manufactured and currently for sale in Asia (www.IWSLR.com), where it has been successfully test marketed for over one year.    The next step is to place a sufficiently large manufacturing order (3,000+ units) to be shipped to the U.S. and available for sale initially on Amazon, and start an on-line advertising campaign. In order to move forward, I am seeking investor funding of approximately $100,000+.     Some information about me: I have an office in Hong Kong, and frequently commute back and forth to the U.S. VINTU, LLC is currently a sole proprietorship, with me, Jerry Tucker, as owner. I have over 20 years of experience in sales and marketing, with a focus in the healthcare industry. I am a registered dietitian, and have previously worked as a sports nutritionist. My profile can be viewed on LinkedIn, at: Jerry L. Tucker (Shanghai, China). In addition, I hold a MBA, as well as a Master degree in nutrition, and have experience as a financial analyst.

Description: Redroom.com is a website teaching users how to make, save, and invest money.
Headquarters Regions: Southern US
Full Description: Red Room builds on a successful, trusted brand: The Red Room Writers Society. For years, writers have joined the Red Room Writers Society to get their writing done in a supportive environment. Most people don't need more instruction; they need to write. The Red Room Writers Society is the only writers society or school focused on writing rather than focused on reading and talking. Founded in June 2002 by Ivory Madison, the Red Room Writers Society began providing its innovative, signature Writers Studios to procrastinating professional and aspiring writers in the San Francisco Bay Area. It was an immediate success. Founded on just $150, and a lot of volunteer support, it provided numerous scholarships for writers who could not otherwise afford the program, as well as numerous donations to silent auctions and community programs. At the same time, it made writers feel special, giving them an inspiring and luxurious environment in the formal dining room of a 1904 mansion. The Red Room Writers Society was recognized by San Francisco magazine in its Best of the Bay 2005.The company has been profiled in the media as a major feature story in statewide publications such as California Lawyer magazine,and in national book industry magazines such as Pages.The company and its founder are deeply entrenched in the San Francisco literary scene. Madison has served on the board of and been a featured writer at Litquake, the city's premiere annual literary festival. The Red Room Writers Society is featured in the citywide Literary Map of San Francisco. While the Red Room Writers Society began with just four members, it now has served more than four hundred talented writers in San Francisco, and appeared in the acknowledgements of published books, by authors who mention that they never would have finished their manuscripts without the Red Room Writers Society. The "brick and mortar" Red Room worked with as many writers as possible through its Writers Studios, workshops, and coaching and editing services, until going on hiatus in August 2008, so that Madison could focus on reaching an even wider community, worldwide.  The internet is the perfect vehicle to connect writers, rich or poor, published or unpublished, to the support and resources they need to make their dreams come true, and so Madison founded redroom.com, which launched to the public in January 2008.
Industry Groups: Content and Publishing, Media and Entertainment

Description: Premium Standard Farms was founded in 1988 with the goal of creating a standardized system to produce premium pork.
Headquarters Regions: Midwestern US
Full Description: Premium Standard Farms was founded in 1988 with the goal of creating a standardized system to produce premium pork. Today, that goal is a reality. Premium Standard Farms is one of the largest pork producers in the country with roughly 212,000 sows in production in Missouri, North Carolina and Texas, and a state of the art processing facility in Milan, Mo., and Clinton, N.C. The company was the first in the industry to pursue full vertical integration. On December 21, 1989 the first Premium Standard Farms litter of seven gilts and four barrows was born at 7:00 a.m. on the Wiles Farm just outside Princeton, Missouri. By 1991, investment partners were in place, and the company began to grow rapidly, completing construction on production units for 80,000 sows and a processing plant by September of 1994.  The company also began expansion in Texas in 1994, acquiring the former National Hog Farms of Texas in June of that year. Additional growth and expansion in Texas was underway in 1995 when the commodity markets experienced unprecedented volatility, forcing a change in strategy and a capital restructuring. By 1996 with the restructuring complete, the Company was on the road to becoming a leader in the industry. In May 1998, Premium Standard Farms merged with Continental Grain Company's (now ContiGroup Companies, Inc.) north Missouri swine operation adding an additional 25,000 sows of production to the existing 80,000 sow Missouri herd. This merger added to the Company's strength, and set the stage for the future. On June 30, 2000 Premium Standard Farms signed an agreement with the Lundy Packing Company to purchase its processing and production operations. It was also announced that Premium Standard Farms would purchase Contigroup's Carolina Farms operations. By August 25, the purchase was complete and both groups are now part of the Premium Standard Farms team. Premium Standard Farms is recognized as an industry leader in food safety, environmental stewardship and worker safety. The company's commitment to quality was recognized in December 1998 when Premium Standard Farms became the first pork producer/processor to earn Process Verified (PVP) accreditation from the United States Department of Agriculture. Today, Premium Standard Farms markets consistent high quality pork to discriminating domestic retailers, further processors, food service providers and export customers in more than 20 countries around the world.

Description: Our goal is simple… to make your travel dreams a reality.
Headquarters Regions: East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: Big Five Tours & Expeditions remains committed to the best practices of sustainable tourism that support cultural heritage, conservation, wildlife and educational initiatives. In 2014, Big Five  was recognized  by Virtuoso, an international luxury travel network, with the award for 2014 Sustainable Tourism Leadership. We received Conde Nast Traveler’s World Savers Award in 2013.  Big Five is also a member of The Global Partnership for Sustainable Tourism Criteria (GSTC Partnership) which works to foster increased understanding of sustainable tourism principles and practices. Big Five has a sustainable vision that encompasses working with companies, accommodations and suppliers who share our corporate philosophy of responsible tourism.  In East Africa, for example, Kenya has for generations been ‘the’ safari destination.  We have all heard about or witnessed scenes of a dozen vehicles surrounding one lion trying to catch a nap.  How do we balance the needs of animals, local communities and visitors?  Each segment is vital to the future survival of the animals, cultures and ecosystems of Africa. We believe that part of the answer can be found in private conservancies such as the Selenkay Conservancy, adjacent to Kenya’s Amboseli National Park. This 15,000-acre private game reserve in the heart of Maasailand admits only 18 visitors per day.  It is one of a growing number of conservancies leading the way in habitat conservation as one of the best solutions to help save Africa’s wild places and the animals that inhabit them for the future generations. We also promote and support destinations such as Namibia, which has sustainability written into its constitution, and Costa Rica, which aims to be the first carbon neutral nation. Big Five Tours & Expeditions’ nonprofit Spirit of Big Five Foundation is dedicated to Supporting Sustainable Tourism for a Better Tomorrow.  www.spiritofbigfive.org Formally launched in 2007 as a 501 3c nonprofit organization, the Spirit of Big Five Foundation seeks to broaden the scope and depth of support to conservation, poverty alleviation, education and healthcare in Africa, Asia, and Central and South America. The foundation grew out of the guiding philosophy of Big Five Tours & Expeditions, a leading luxury tour operator. It is a continuation and evolution of our commitment to responsible travel that harks back to its origin of Big Five in Nairobi, Kenya. The founder and CEO, Mahen Sanghrajka, became part of a group  of tour operators who established some a code of ethics for safaris such as prohibiting smoking while on safaris, and forbidding guides and drivers to harass the wildlife.  Today those ideas seems obvious, however, in early 1970s in East Africa, they were not. The operation of the Spirit of Big Five Foundation is entirely funded by the Sanghrajka family, the founders of Big Five Tours & Expeditions.  But many of our guests returning home from their journeys are also inspired to be part of the solution.  We welcome guest donations, and the foundation guarantees that 100% of any donation made goes directly to project(s) selected. We support select projects and programs around the world, demonstrating how tourism can play a positive role in protecting nature and sustaining the well-being of local communities. Foundation funding for projects operates in two ways. First, it makes direct donations to charitable organizations, including humanitarian assistance during natural disaster, such as the January 2010 earthquake in Haiti. Secondly, it also disperses small project grants to grassroots non-profit organizations that meet its funding criteria. Primary goals of the Spirit of Big Five Foundation are:     Conservation and protection of biodiversity, wildlife and natural habitat consistent with sustainable tourism practices.     Support for poverty alleviation and community development, including capacity building, education, and healthcare in tourism destinations.     Support for cultural heritage, archaeological and historical preservation in and around tourism destinations.     Promotion of sustainable tourism principles and best practice Join us as we seek out solutions that positively impact the world today and our children’s world tomorrow.

Description: Wrisco Industries offers a wide variety of aluminum, steel and sheet metal products and services to better meet your demanding needs.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Miami Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: Wrisco Industries Inc. proudly celebrated its 100thAnniversary in 2016. Wrisco’s history traces its origins back to 1916 when the Company was founded as The Guarantee Specialty Manufacturing Company.  From its inception, the Company offered diverse product lines, including uniform fasteners, small washers, specialty stampings, sink strainers, caulking guns and venetian blind components. Over the next forty years, The Guarantee Specialty Manufacturing Company expanded into eleven separate corporations whose products included specialty metal products and various types of extrusions for both the architectural and signage industries along with one-inch and two-inch venetian blind components. During the mid-1970s, these eleven corporations merged under one corporation, RHW, Inc. and were organized into divisions rather than individual companies.  In 1981, RHW, Inc. divested itself of the manufacturing group.  One year later, two of its executives, A. James Monastra and Carl A. Pope, purchased the remaining Wrisco divisions through a holding company, Royalton Products Corporation.  In December 1986, the holding company and operating company were merged into a single entity which maintained the name of the former operating subsidiary, Wrisco Industries Inc. In late 1987, the Corporate Offices were moved from North Royalton, Ohio to its present location in Palm Beach Gardens, Florida. In 1992, Carl A. Pope retired and A. James Monastra became sole owner and consolidated Wrisco into the four divisions that operate at present – Atlanta, Chicago, Dallas and Edison, NJ. Joining A. James Monastra as owners in 2006, is the current team of Jim Monastra President, Roman Bender Vice President and Richard Young Vice President. For more than 100 years, as the industry leader, Wrisco’s mission has been to supply its customers with unmatched quality aluminum products and superior services.   By providing Wrisco’s employees a safe, enjoyable and rewarding workplace, Wrisco constantly meets and surpasses their customer’s expectations. Their sincere gratitude to all that have contributed to Wrisco’s success – past, present and future!

Headquarters Regions: Greater Seattle Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Skillet Street Food In 2007, Chef Josh Henderson created Skillet Street Food in Seattle, one of the first food experiences of what has since become a prototype for the national street food movement that has swept the country. Out of a vintage Airstream trailer, he created innovative lunch menus based on American-inspired food prepared with classic technique and seasonal ingredients. The reception from Seattle'ites was immediate and passionate. They were drawn to the chef-driven food, the excitement of being a part of a new, energetic, urban experience, and to the intimate involvement through the use of social media channels that intensified the connection with the Skillet brand. Since then, the business has grown up. They are still creating great menus served throughout the streets of Seattle from the Airstream. But Skillet is now much more than that. Supported by an outstanding team of almost 100 talented people, They are a thriving catering enterprise, supporting weddings, private parties, and corporate events throughout the Pacific Northwest. They are a food products business, distributing our signature Bacon Jam product through retailers across the US and Canada. And They are cooking more Skillet deliciousness every day at our three restaurants: the Skillet Diner in Seattle's Capitol Hill neighborhood, the Skillet: Counter located in the Armory at the Seattle Center, and our newest Skillet Diner located in Ballard. The original street food business has become a brand but has not strayed from its roots. The thread is still there: great food prepared with care, technique and the best of ingredients; an innovative experience that consistently surprises and satisfies; and a feeling of being personally connected to Skillet, in all its manifestations. They see this as our mission - to continue to deliver on these themes and to continue to find new channels though which They can expand the brand and the family of loyal Skillet customers.

Description: Camiant is a provider of policy control and application assurance technologies.
Headquarters Regions: Greater Boston Area, East Coast, New England
Full Description: Camiant, Inc. provides policy control and application assurance technology. It offers Multimedia Policy Engine, a central component of the broadband network, which provides real-time intelligence and control; and Bandwidth on Demand Application Manager for the integration of new applications into the access networks. The company also provides SIP Application Manager that enables network providers to integrate and manage SIP resources within the architectural framework of access networks; and QInsight management reporting application, which collects usage information and provides perspectives on network usage over time, subscriber tier distribution, and various key metrics. In addition, it offers Universal Edge Resource Manager for managing the sharing of edge resources among multiple services, including video on demand and switched digital video; and Fair Use Management solution, which enables cable operators to manage broadband utilization. The company serves broadband operators in Europe, the Middle East, and the Asia Pacific. Camiant, Inc. was formerly known as Chameleon Solutions, Inc.
Top 5 Investors: Matrix, North Bridge Venture Partners & Growth Equity, Pilot House Ventures

Full Description: We develop and deliver 3D cameras for the dimensional inspection market.  Our Orbiter3D camera head can recover 3D profiles in seconds, and can be a building block for complex inspection stations. Our Orbiter3D-360 is an integrated scanner to recover full 3D model of an object below 15x15x15 cm. Potential applications are in the semiconductor, electronics, automotive, aerospace and medical devices industries.  We have partnered with Rapidform software to deliver complete solutions for 3D modeling, 3D measurement tools and Reverse engineering from 3D scans tools.  We have the expertise to build applications around our technology suited to your inspection needs.
